relevant_communication:
As team leader and expert in national and European projects on qualifications frameworks, I laid the foundation for  the National Qualifications Framework for Higher Education in Romania, by elaborating and implementing the Methodology and the National Qualification Register and its portal.   
As General director of National Qualifications Authority  (NQA) of Romania I undertaken the following activities: 
▪    Contributing to the elaboration of public policies and legislation regarding the NQF implementation, higher education and adult education in Romania; 
▪    Ensuring the effective representation and public relations of the NQA at national level; 
▪    Ensuring the effective representation of the NQA at European level, working closely with the European institutions and bodies, including DG Education , Audiovisual and  Culture (DG EAC), European Centre for the Development for Vocational Training (CEDEFOP)  and European Training Foundation (ETF); 
▪    Ensuring the effective representation of the NQA at international level, including cooperation with World Bank, OECD;  
▪    Romanian representative in the EQF Advisory Group and national correspondent for Qualification Framework (QF) for European Higher Education Area (EHEA). 

Since 1994, I have worked in a multicultural environment improving the Romanian educational system through projects for higher education management reform and the improvement of the quality of education. Moreover, I have cooperated with universities and other educational bodies and employers mainly from France, Ireland, Spain, Germany, Malta, Italy, UK, but also with European institutions. All the co operations mentioned below were developed throughout more than 40 research and training projects within the European programmes: Phare, RICOP, Jean Monnet, Socrates, Leonardo da Vinci, Lifelong Learning and European Social Fund for implementing European strategies moreover the Bologna and Copenhagen Processes. 
I managed applied researches into: education management, graduate labour market insertion, the partnership between education and social and economic environment, development of entrepreneurial university, adult learning and qualification frameworks within the projects or actions founded by EC. 
I am the author of  2 PhD thesis, 125 articles published in Scientific Journals and Proceedings of national or international conferences  and of 34 books or proceedings.  
 Some examples :  
